Package org.cesecore.authorization.user.matchvalues

Enum AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry>
      • org.cesecore.authorization.user.matchvalues.AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry>
    public enum AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry
extends Enum<AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry>
    This enum-pattern singleton acts as a lookup registry for AccessMatchValue implementations. Any AccessMatchValue willing to be used has to register itself and its token type here.
    Version:
    $Id: AccessMatchValueReverseLookupRegistry.java 25313 2017-02-21 20:51:59Z jeklund $

      • performReverseLookup

        public AccessMatchValue performReverseLookup​(String tokenType,
                                             int databaseValue)
        This method performs a reverse lookup given a token type and an integer, by using already registered callback method to translate those values into an AccessMatchValue. If no corresponding callback method has been registered, this method will return null.
        Parameters:
        tokenType - A string identifier
        databaseValue - the numeric value from the database.
        Returns:
        The AccessMatchValue-extending enum returned by the corresponding lookup method, null if token type isn't registered.
